gecandeias","ctime_ts":1281455401,"tracked":0},{"shown":1,"collapsed":0,"userpic":"http://l-userpic.livejournal.com/93630461/40274","actions":[{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/172311.html?replyto=10928919","name":"reply","title":"Reply","footer":1},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/172311.html?thread=10928919#t10928919","name":"permalink","title":"link"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/172311.html?thread=10928919#t10928919","name":"collapse","title":"Collapse"},{"allowed":1,"href":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/172311.html?thread=10928919#t10928919","name":"expand","title":"Expand"}],"uname":"blipangel","loaded":1,"p_tracked":0,"commenter_journal_base":"http://blipangel.livejournal.com/","statprefix":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net","dtalkid":10928919,"talkid":42691,"thread_url":"http://grrm.livejournal.com/172311.html?thread=10928919#t10928919","upictitle":"godspeed balance: Starks","article":"Bakker's books are amazing.  After I finished Feast for Crows I started on the Prince of Nothing series and have just begun the fourth book...  His writing often takes me back to literary crit classes in college: Lacan, Derrida and various philosophical works that go into modern deconstruction.  He plays with signifier/signified with Kelhus quite a bit, which gives the character a depth few others achieve in the genre.  Scott does a tremendous job of marrying intellectually stimulating content with some of the easy access primal sex and violence that drive his stories...  I would think that many of your fans would enjoy the Prince of Nothing series!<br /><br />Do you count him among your friends?  Stay in touch?","siteroot":"http://www.livejournal.com","poster":"grrm","stime":"6 years ago","ctime":"August 10 2010, 18:26:21 UTC","massactions":0,"subject":"R. Scott Bakker = YES","deleted":0,"username":[{"journal_url":"http://blipangel.livejournal.com/","striked":null,"journaltype":"P","userhead_url":"http://l-stat.livejournal.net/img